<td valign="top" class="postbody">
<hr />
Okay, first let me apologize cause this is going to be kind of long.  Sorry.
<br />

<br />
This is the story as told to me by my mother in law.  
<br />

<br />
When my husband was a baby, his family was on vacation and they had stopped for gas and were back on the highway when the axle broke on the car.  My hubby had been sitting on his grandma's lap when this happened and they both went thru the windshield.  Sadly, his grandma died instantly.  My hubby was in a coma for three days, his forehead was badly swollen,had two broken legs, his tongue had been cut by the glass (he is now 33 and still has a gash in his tongue) and he had seizures during his childhood as a result of the brain injury.  
<br />
My mother in law told me that while she was packing the car, someone whispered in her ear&quot; Say Goodbye&quot;, and then as they were getting back in the car after getting gas that she had the most intense feeling of dread and then the accident happened. 
<br />
 
<br />
Okay fast forward about 8 years.  My hubby is the oldest of 5 kids, so the other 4 children were not born until after grandma passed.  So hubby's sister is about 3 yrs. old and she starts telling mother in law that some lady is always talking to her, mom doesn't think anything of it, until sister says that the lady wants to know &quot;how is Michael's head?&quot; Well my hubby is Michael and remember his forehead was swollen and he had been in a coma.  
<br />

<br />
I totally believe that it was grandma making sure that Mike was okay after the horrific car accident.  
<br />

<br />
Sorry it was so long, but I wanted to share that with you all.
<br />

<br />
Sarah77</td>
